</taxonomicName>
, male, slide No. CMT16115W (Scale = 1.0 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3219E90687BFFF3FF2513BBFC83F9A9" pageId="1" pageNumber="348" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B84CD1B687BFFF3FF2513BBFC83F9A9" blockId="1.[151,1436,1465,1598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis id="B94F1109687BFFF3FF2513BBFEC0FA45" bold="true" box="[199,315,1465,1490]" pageId="1" pageNumber="348">Remarks.</emphasis>
The narrow forewing of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3BB698687BFFF3FD8413B8FD23FA46" box="[614,728,1466,1489]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Pityocona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94F1109687BFFF3FD8413B8FD23FA46" box="[614,728,1466,1489]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="348">Pityocona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with several distinct black spots and the male genitalia with bifurcate uncus make 
<taxonomicName id="4C3BB698687BFFF3FE6D13DCFDFAFA62" box="[399,513,1502,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Pityocona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94F1109687BFFF3FE6D13DCFDFAFA62" box="[399,513,1502,1525]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="348">Pityocona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinguishable from its most closely related genera. The diagnostic characters of this genus include the bifurcate uncus, the valva curved approximately beyond middle and extending inward distally, and the extremely narrow vinculum in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
